@page
@model BudgetPilot.Pages.PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<section class="py-5">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Last updated: May 29, 2025</p>

    <h2>1. About This Project</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>BudgetPilot</strong> is a diploma web project by Miron Ryzleytsev, 
      student of group 545a, Department of Computer Systems and Networks (CSN), 
      at Kharkiv Aviation University. Its goal is to provide a simple, secure tool 
      to manage personal finances: create multiple wallets (accounts), record transactions, 
      and generate reports and visualizations.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Your email and hashed password via ASP.NET Identity when you register.</li>
      <li><strong>Financial Data:</strong> Details of your wallets and transactions (date, amount, category, description).</li>
      <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Page visits and actions, for improving the application.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How We Use Your Data</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Authenticate and authorize your access.</li>
      <li>Perform CRUD operations on wallets and transactions.</li>
      <li>Generate analytics and exportable reports.</li>
      <li>Send important notifications (e.g. password reset links).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Cookies and Session</h2>
    <p>
      BudgetPilot uses only essential cookies for authentication (ASP.NET Core). 
      No third-party tracking or analytical cookies are used.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Data Storage and Security</h2>
    <p>
      All communication is secured via SSL/TLS, and passwords are stored as hashes. 
      While we follow industry best practices, no method of data transmission or storage 
      is 100% secure.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Data Sharing</h2>
    <p>
      We do not sell, rent, or share your personal data with third parties, 
      except as required by law.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Access:</strong> You may view or export your data at any time.</li>
      <li><strong>Correction:</strong> You may edit your wallets and transactions freely.</li>
      <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> You may delete your account; all associated data will be permanently removed.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>8. Contact & Institution</h2>
    <p>
      This diploma project is part of the curriculum at 
      <a href="https://khai.edu/ua/" target="_blank">Kharkiv Aviation University</a>, 
      Department of Computer Systems and Networks (CSN).  
      For questions or feedback, please email  
      <a href="mailto:m.r.ryzleytsev@student.csn.khai.edu">m.r.ryzleytsev@student.csn.khai.edu</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
